The general approach is „from bench to bedside“ . The theoretical knowledge obtained will be fortified by real life patients at the rheumatology ward. Rheumatoid arthritis, spondyloarthropathies, diffuse connective tissue diaseases (systemic lupus, systemic sclerosis, vasculitides, dermato- and polymyositis), metabolic and degenerative musculoskeletal conditions (osteoarthritis, osteoporosis, gout) will be focused on. Also genetic and infectious factors for rheumatic diseases will be analyzed. The main rheumatologic emergencies will be discussed with appropriate management algorithms.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to provide students the basic competency in the field of rheumatology: the scope of common rheumatic diseases, their etiology, pathogenesis, diagnosing, differential diagnosis and treatment. In addition to theoretical aspects the students will obtain practical skills in the clinical investigation, treatment and monitoring of rheumatic patients.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of the course the students will be able to 1)specify the symptoms and signs, epidemiology, etiology and pathogenesis of major rheumatic diseases; 2) demonstrate practical skills in acquiring a complete history and physical examination of a rheumatic patients; 3) differentiate between normal and pathology physical, laboratory and radiological findings in rheumatic diseases 4) describe the major indications, adverse events, interactions and contraindications of commonly used drugs in the managment of rheumatic diseases 5) outline the health and economic impact and prognosis/outcome of musculosceletal conditions
